---
title: "File Update Strategy — Rewrite vs Merge vs Surgical"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as User
    participant S as Skill
    participant D as Dispatcher
    participant FS as FileSystem

    U->>S: update request (area / file target)

    S->>FS: read existing file (if any)
    FS-->>S: content or "not found"

    S->>D: classify(file_type)

    alt JSON state file
        note over D: component-registry.json<br/>frontend-analysis.json
        D-->>S: strategy = MERGE
        S->>S: load existing records
        S->>S: overwrite status="unverified" entries
        S->>S: preserve figma_connected=true records
        S->>FS: write merged JSON
        FS-->>S: ok
    else Derived .md artefact
        note over D: reference-*.md<br/>rules/frontend-*.md<br/>*.mmd diagrams
        D-->>S: strategy = FULL_REWRITE
        S->>S: build fresh content from JSON
        S->>FS: write (overwrite)
        FS-->>S: ok
    else CLAUDE.md section
        note over D: ### Frontend subsection<br/>under ## Architecture
        D-->>S: strategy = SURGICAL
        S->>FS: read CLAUDE.md
        FS-->>S: full content
        S->>S: locate target section bounds
        S->>S: replace section body only
        S->>FS: write CLAUDE.md
        FS-->>S: ok
    else File does not exist
        note over D: any type, first run
        D-->>S: strategy = CREATE
        S->>S: build full content
        S->>FS: write new file
        FS-->>S: ok
    end

    S-->>U: report(strategy used, path, line count)
